Citation.sAbstract: Solubility data were measured for succinimide in pure ethyl acetate, acetonitrile, ethanol,  acetone, tetrahydrofuran, methanol, isopropanol, n-butanol and binary methanol+ethyl acetate solvent  mixtures at the temperature range between 278.2K and 325.1K under atmospheric pressure by  gravimetric method. The solubilities of succinimide in those selected solvents increased with  increasing temperature. The solubility data were correlated with the modified Apelblat equation to  obtain the model parameters. The experimental results could be useful for optimizing the process of  purification of succinimide in industry. Methanol could be the excellent solvent in the crystallization of  succinimide.
Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of succinimide in different pure solvents and binary methanol+ethyl acetate solvent  mixtures
